Priority pollutant greenhouse gases
* The following greenhouse gases are declared priority air pollutants:
<\li1>
	* Carbon dioxide (CO2);
	* Methane (CH4);
	* Nitrous oxide (N2O);
	* Hydrofluorocarbons (HFCs);
	* Perf1uorocarbons (PFCs); and
	* Sulphur hexafluoride (SFs).

List of production processes
* Coal mining;
* Production and/or refining of crude oil;
* Production and/or processing of natural gas;
* Production of liquid fuels from coal or gas;
* Cement production;
	* Glass production;
	* Ammonia production;
	* Ammonia production;
 (h} Nitric acid production;
	* Carbon black production;
	* Iron and steel production;
	* Ferro-alloys production;
	* Aluminium production (excluding foundries);
	* Polymers production;
	* Pulp and paper production;
	* (combustion of fossil fuels, excluding the use of back-up generators).
